ebp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1106%2C738 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1660%2C1107 3x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(max-width: 589px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=553%2C369, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1106%2C738 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1660%2C1107 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 992px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1238%2C826 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1858%2C1239 3x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 992px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1238%2C826 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1858%2C1239 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=406%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=814%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1222%2C815 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1630%2C1087 4x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=406%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=814%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1222%2C815 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1630%2C1087 4x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1109%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1666%2C1111 3x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1109%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1666%2C1111 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Man cycling on a smart trainer\" title=\"TrainerRoad\" src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/TrainerRoad_KK_1224-2885c4d.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413\"></picture></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> Every athlete is different and following a stock training plan doesn’t work for everyone. TrainerRoad’s new Adaptive Training tool is designed to solve this problem.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>TrainerRoad</i></span></p></div><ul><li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-smart-trainer/\">Best smart trainers</a></li></ul><p>In contrast, when you sign up with a real life cycling coach, they will help optimise your training load, fitness progression and training specificity, as well as adjust your future workouts to help you manage the rest of life’s challenges.</p><p>The downside is that a human coach can often be relatively expensive because this personal touch requires a lot of expertise and time investment.</p><p>TrainerRoad’s new Adaptive Training tool seems to suggest it can provide the best of both worlds, combining the accessibility of online training plans with the adaptability and personalised nature of a real-life coach.</p><p>Exactly how well it works in practice remains to be seen, of course, but it’s undoubtedly an exciting prospect.</p><h2>When will Adaptive Training be available?</h2><p>The Adaptive Training feature is currently in closed beta, and TrainerRoad has not confirmed a precise release date. It does say, however, that individual aspects of the tool will begin rolling out soon, “starting with TrainNow and data-driven updates to existing TrainerRoad training plans.”</p><p>For those who can’t wait, TrainerRoad says subscribers keen to get early access to the new tools can request priority access via <a href=\"https://www.trainerroad.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">TrainerRoad.com</a>.</p></section><section><h3>Authors</h3><section><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/author/bromleysimon/\"><img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/06/Simon-Bromley_Profile-Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585-d34f7eb-scaled.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=60,60\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/06/Simon-Bromley_Profile-Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585-d34f7eb-scaled.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=120,120 120w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/06/Simon-Bromley_Profile-Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585-d34f7eb-scaled.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=60,60 60w,\" sizes=\"(max-width: 60px) 100vw, 60px\" width=\"60\" height=\"60\" alt=\"Simon Bromley_Profile Pic\" title=\"Simon Bromley_Profile Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585\"></a><p>Simon is a writer and photographer who has been riding bikes for fun since he was a kid. He took a deep dive into road racing, crits and time trial culture in his twenties, but as a person of very little talent, he always looks to tech to compensate. He loves nothing more than finding a smart (preferably cheap) hack that others hadn’t thought of. His stable of bikes isn’t the most extravagant, but they’re all customised to meet Simon’s particular tastes and kept fastidiously clean.</p></section></section></div>","author":"Simon Bromley","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"fbd4f9ad60ad1521c7d0402cbc131397ef6b03bf0a54827a2f75dbd4136cf305","category":"Cycling"}